No information.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="36" pageNumber="520" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="36.[147,1354,285,518]" pageId="36" pageNumber="520">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[150,502,363,396]" pageId="36" pageNumber="520">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Data Deficient on The IUCN Red List. Cadena’s Tailless Bat is endemic to a small region with high rates of agricultural transformation; therefore,its populations could be declining because of habitat loss.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
